# npm 11.11.0 — transitive dependency CVEs (no upstream fix available)
#
# These are bundled inside npm itself. We do not control the transitive
# versions; they will be fixed when a new npm release updates its deps.
# All three are DoS-class issues in minimatch/tar that require crafted
# input, carrying no practical risk in a CI context with trusted inputs.

# minimatch: ReDoS via unbounded recursive backtracking (fixed in 10.2.3)
CVE-2026-27903

# minimatch: ReDoS via catastrophic backtracking in glob expressions (fixed in 10.2.3)
CVE-2026-27904

# node-tar: vulnerability in tar <7.5.10
CVE-2026-29786
